definitions.definition: The mast nearest the bow , on a sailing ship with more than one mast or a non-sailing ship with any masts; the second-tallest mast on a full-rigged ship.

main_definition: ( nautical ) The mast nearest the bow , on a sailing ship with more than one mast or a non-sailing ship with any masts; the second-tallest mast on a full-rigged ship.
